    public abstract static class TokenStringFormat.Token<T>

      • Token

        protected Token(TokenStringFormat<?> rParent,
                java.lang.String sToken,
                java.lang.String sFormat)
        Creates a new token with a certain parent token string format and format string. The format string argument will be parsed with the method parseFormat(String). Tokens of subclassed formats should always be created with this constructor to allow the correct creation of nested formats.
        Parameters:
        rParent - The parent format of this token
        sToken - The string description of the token
        sFormat - The format string for this token

      • transform

        public final java.lang.String transform(T rInput)
        Transforms the input value into a string that can be inserted into the resulting string of a string token transformation. Returns the result of the applyFormat(Object) method that has been invoked on the return value of the extractValue(Object) method. If the input value is a collection or an array the format will be applied to each element in the array and the resulting strings will be concatenated.
        Parameters:
        rInput - The input value of the token string transformation
        Returns:
        The result of transforming this token into a string derived from the input value

        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • applyFormat

        protected java.lang.String applyFormat(java.lang.Object rValue)
        Subclasses can override this method to apply a specific format to the value that has been returned by extractValue(Object). The default implementation handles the following types of format objects:
        • String: returns String.format((String) Format, rValue)
        • TokenStringFormat: returns Format.transform(rValue)
        • java.text.Format: returns Format.format(rValue)
        • Other types or NULL: returns rValue.toString()
        Parameters:
        rValue - The value that has been extracted from the input
        Returns:
        A string containing the formatted string representing the input value

      • parseFormat

        protected java.lang.Object parseFormat(java.lang.String sFormat)
        Can be overridden by subclasses that support different formats to implement the parsing of format strings. The default implementation provides support for several format types as described in the main class documentation.
        Parameters:
        sFormat - The format string (must not be NULL)
        Returns:
        The object representing the parsed format
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the argument doesn't contain a recognized format or parsing it fails

      • setFormatObject

        protected final void setFormatObject(java.lang.Object rFormatObject)
        Sets the format object that will be used to format input values. Can be used by subclasses to set a specific format instead of parsing it from a string.
        Parameters:
        rFormatObject - The new format object
